function M = PasteCImage% M = PasteCImage% % Paste the clipboard into matrix M.  The clipboard should be a PICT.% M comes out as an color image. After multiplying by 255 it should for% be suitable for Screen 'PutImage'.% % The PICT should represent a square image, otherwise there are no% guarantees about what will happen. PasteCImage does not handle% non-square images, but should.  A little effort would do it.% % The bug reported for PasteImage probably applies equally to% PasteCImage.% % Also see PasteImage, CopyImage, Screen.% 8/19/94		dhb		Link in new pixmap handling code.% 8/4/00		dgp		Mention PasteImage bug.